name: michael-and-silvija

text: Hello Silvija, it’s an absolute pleasure to meet you! :D I’m Mike haha!

Good Evening Mike, 

My name is Silvija and I am a 2nd year student in University of West London. 

I am uncredibly happy to be working with you! :)
Amazing! Well where to start haha :)  I work at Framestore, in the Lighting/Texture department! I have been here for almost 3 years; starting off as a Runner and working my way up!
Oh and I graduated in 2016 from Teesside University where I studied Computer Animation and VFX

Woow! Superb! It sounds like so much fun!  :fire::fire::fire:

I was not very informative on my side, haha :D 

I am studying VFx, I am from Lithuania, so if there will be something, that I will sound not clear about, please do tell me!
At the moment I do study and I am working full time in a pet boutique ( so I am quite knowledgeable about the animals behaviour and etc) haha:D

Oooohh it is a lot of fun!! Haha! That’s all alright, I’m unsure how best you want to communicate, whether you prefer chat or trying to setup a video chat, to go through what you want to get out of the mentoring!
I love animals haha
I’m from Wales, grew up with lots of dogs and cats :) so I could hear about animals all day haha
How’s you’re second year going so far?

Oh, I am very sorry, I am still familiarizing with the app and the system. 

I would love to setup a video chat! 

Unfortunetaly, I am not in a house at the moment. I would not be able to have a video chat at the moment. 
But definetally tomorrow evening, if you would be available! 
I am very sorry about it. 

Animals are incredible, haha :D I could talk about them all day, hahaha 

My second year is doing great! It is quite hard to work and study, but doing my best! 
We started doing Nuke, which seemed a little complicated at the beginning, but is getting better. 
Character animation in Maya is so much fun, but it seems quite difficult, as there has to be so much knowledge about human movements!
But definetaly, this year is very very exciting!:heart_eyes:
Same here, new to using this too, unsure if they have a call feature, but if not we can try Skype or something! Get the ball rolling for you!
Ahhhh so many new things to learn!!! No problem I can run you down with what to learn for industry so you aren’t wasting you’re valuable time! And yes super exciting!! :bear:
Do you know what you want to sort of specialise in or a department you’d love to learn more about?
Sorry if delay in replying, travelling home :)

I am very sorry as well, I was using underground. x) 

Skype sound perfect! 

Thank you very much for lending me your tine and knowledge! 

I love 3D modelling, but when we started Nuke, I realised editing is soooo much fun as well!  
I really do struggle with lightening and texturing. I believe these are one of my major areas, that I need to learn more about.

I started trying to make a little animation (I know it takes a lot of people to do it properly, but I love challenges, hahaha).
It is about a little snowman trying to fight the sun :sun_with_face: I will tell you more about it during the video chat, if you would like to hear it.

Anyway, I was really struggling with a snow texturing as well as lightening. Could not get it rendered as well :s
Which department did you want to do, when you were  in University?:)
yes the packed underground :stuck_out_tongue: I use the bus now! can actually breath!
its no trouble, wished I had this opportunity in university, wouldve been so useful!!!
aaahh so you want to get a broader sense of the pipeline before deciding what you love to do more? and I can mostr definatly help you improve youre lighting/texture/lookdev
would love to hear more about youre ideas :slightly_smiling_face:
I didnt really know what I wanted to get into till end of my second year
I absolutly love look development and adding all the textures and shading the asset to look like real life!!, never really thought texturing as a fun job as not many people wanted to get into it
but its amazing, getting to work on so many different pieces everyday
on Paddington 2 I was working on the pop up sequence, then his barber jacket, then a plant hahaha
I maybe unable to skype tomorrow, I can during my lunch hour 1-2, just let me know what works for you! :slightly_smiling_face:

Isn't it? Underground could be very tiresome, haha

I am very happy to be able to ask someone, who works industry, questions and feedback :heart_eyes:
Yes, I still try to look more into the pipeline, it is quite big as well, haha
 
To be honest, at the beggining, I never knew how important was to make proper lighting and textures. Once I started looking and trying more, I realised , haha:D 

It is really pleasuring as well to see how simple things can change so dramatically!

Wooow! Really on Paddington? That is amazing!!!
Was it difficult?

I am working all the way till 6pm. But any day after 6pm (Thursdays after 7pm) is perfectly fine with me! So, whenever you would be available! 
I will prepare some question tomorrow then, will use my chance to ask you questions, haha :D
indeed, how long have you lived in London? :slightly_smiling_face:
yeaaaah the vfx pipeline is huge and lots of areas to explore!
lighting and texture can really help make a piece of work! thats why I love it so much
yes Paddington was my first show I worked on; it was such a big learning curve and worked along side so many other talented artists!
it was only difficult as I wanted to impress; as I came from Running at the time!
awesome! we can continue to try :slightly_smiling_face: I've also sorta written down some topics that may help with youre questions!

Im unfamiliar with youre courses modules and what youre final will entile! during mine it was a personal final year project and a group project, so I put alot of work into my personal to be able to show my lighting/lookdev
we can discuss more about that another time though! :slightly_smiling_face:

In London I am only for 2 years :smile:
It is a huge and very busy city, haha

I bet it was quite a challenge being a runner!
Yeah, Paddington is a great piece :+1:

As far as we know, in the final project we will have to make only our personal project, which we would use for the showreels as well.  Generally, my group is really small, only 7 people in the 2nd year, hahaha:D 

But yeah, I wish to do making my own stuff :D 

But yeah, whenever you would be available, just please text me! 

Thank you !
about the same time as me then! :slightly_smiling_face: haha yeah its super busy all the time! aww thank you :slightly_smiling_face: appreciate it!
aah wonderful, so we later down the line we can really focus on what we want to do for youre final piece as I remember it was quite a daunting decision
oh wow, thats probably a good thing to have a small year group haha
now, do you have any work from youre first year or recent work I can take a look at?

Wooow, really :o
 
Yes, it is very good:D 

Yes, I do have a simple renders, if that would be okay!
why yes of course! :slightly_smiling_face:
lemme send you my showreel from my final year of university
Please do!
<https://vimeo.com/170326781>

One sec
I will send my little jobs
oh nooooo you can do so much better!
and you will :smile:
With your help, I will do my best, haha:D
sure thing!
whats youre current module for uni? :slightly_smiling_face:
At the moment we do , The Composite, Character Animation and Digital Sculpture, so we only recently started using Zbrush and Nuke, so as animating in Maya.
Well, everything is pretty random, I am sorry :D
The last onewith a Bump cars, was my first year first project
(Chernobyl) hahaha
Looks funny:D I was just trying to unserstand how textures works:D
bloody hell!!!! this is awesome work! dont be at all sorry haha
and for some of it have been from youre first year, even better! just shows how much you have learnt
love the little robot!
even the eyeball, great work on the sclera, its quite tricky!
this has made even more excited to get started haha!! :space_invader:
what software are you using for youre texture work? :slightly_smiling_face:

Really? Thank you so much!!! 

I love that little robot as well, even called him little Jaspy :D :D :D 

I am trying to use Substance Painter, what software do you use?
ooooooooooooo
thats what I wanted to hear :smile:
Substance is starting to become a great software to use at work!
more of us are using it
we use Mari/Photoshop/Substance and sometimes Nuke!
little Japsy hahaha, awesome! :smile:
and yes to me youre showing so much diversity in everything! which is great to see
shading, texture, modelling, the works

I tried painting texture for the eye in Zbrush, but yeah, substance seems to be so useful, you can get really good effects :o

Yeah, I was trying to learn some more of after effects, so little Jaspy is being my trial. I tried to input him into the an image that I just tooks, haha

Thank you very much! Please tell me all the critics as well!  I do know it is far from good tho, hahaha :D
It was a competition in my area, so I experimented with Jaspy
Far from perfect, but it was really fun playing with After Effects
Hahaha
oh yeah zbrush is probably best for sculpting, and substance is really good to get some really decent first pass textures out there :slightly_smiling_face:
I will have to look up Mari as well! Never really heard of it :o
after effects was my go to software in uni! my final year project was composited using it!
just like the layer system haha
aaahh I see! well that takes really well
Mari is probably the number 1 software a texture artist would use, I can look around and find the best tutorials to start with
if you wanted to
actually.... orrrrrr... maybe give you a demo on them, substance and mari, just the basics
shall write that idea down :bear:

Yes please! I would really appreciate it! 

Very excited to try!

Wooow! Thank you so much!
Hahha, I am really excited :grin:
coolio! :slightly_smiling_face: is anyone else in youre part of the mentoring?
Like other people in my class? Sorry, I could not really understand the question :disappointed_relieved:
oh yeah in youre call
*class
sorry, forgot to add that part! haha
Happens, haha, I believe no one else. I do know someone from 1st year has applied for mentoring as well

aaahhh so you'll have quite the edge :stuck_out_tongue: coolio! well we shall have to organize a call, like I said if you can do 1-2 anytiome that would be so great! if not we can arrange it for Thursday for 7ish? :slightly_smiling_face: its getting late, not enough time in the day!!! have a lovely rest of you're evening! and speak soon!

Thank you again! I will try my best to available between 1-2 for 30 mins at least. If not, then definetally Thrusday 7-ish.
Have some good rest! Good night :crescent_moon:
